// PreviewTab
// Full-screen preview tab for mobile with an item-picker drawer.
// Shows MermaidPreview for diagrams or MarkdownPreview for documents.
// Auto-opens the drawer when no item is selected but items exist.

FUNCTION PreviewTab(className) -> JSX                                  EXPORT
  CALLS: MermaidPreview (MermaidPreview), MarkdownPreview (MarkdownPreview),
         ItemDrawer (ItemDrawer), useDataLoader (useDataLoader)
  Reads diagrams, documents, selectedDiagramId, selectedDocumentId,
  currentSession from sessionStore.
  1. Builds a combined items array (diagrams + documents) sorted by
     lastModified.
  2. Derives selectedItem from selectedDiagramId or selectedDocumentId.
  3. IF no selectedItem and items exist, opens the drawer automatically.
  4. Renders a top bar with type icon, item name, and "Browse" button (only
     when an item is selected).
  5. Renders preview content: MermaidPreview for diagrams,
     MarkdownPreview (collapsibleSections) for documents, or an empty state
     with a "Browse Items" button.
  6. Always renders ItemDrawer (hidden when closed).

---

FUNCTION getItemTypeIcon() -> JSX
  Returns diagram icon SVG if selectedItem is a diagram; document icon
  otherwise.

---

FUNCTION handleItemSelect(item) -> void
  CALLS: selectDiagramWithContent (useDataLoader), selectDocumentWithContent (useDataLoader)
  IF item is a diagram, calls selectDiagramWithContent. ELSE selectDocumentWithContent.
  Closes the drawer.
